\sin\theta\geq 0
 \sin^2\theta+\cos^2\theta=1\quad\Rightarrow\quad|\sin\theta|=\sqrt{1-\cos^2\theta}=\sqrt{1-1/k^2}=\frac{\sqrt{k^2-1}}{|k|}. 
 \sin\theta = \frac{\sqrt{k^2-1}}{-k}\quad\Rightarrow\quad \csc\theta=-\frac{k}{\sqrt{k^2-1}}. 
